<item>
            <title>[SPARK-34053] Please reduce GitHub Actions matrix or improve the build time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-34053</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GitHub Actions queue is very high for Apache projects, and it looks like a significant number of executors are occupied by Spark jobs &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: all Apache projects share the same limit of shared GitHub Actions runners, and based on the chart below Spark is consuming 20+ runners while the total limit (for all ASF projects) is 180.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r5303eec41cc1dfc51c15dbe44770e37369330f9644ef09813f649120%40%3Cbuilds.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r5303eec41cc1dfc51c15dbe44770e37369330f9644ef09813f649120%40%3Cbuilds.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;number of GA workflows in/progress/queued per project and they clearly show the situation is getting worse by day: &lt;a href=&quot;https://pasteboard.co/JIJa5Xg.png&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://pasteboard.co/JIJa5Xg.png&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
